Description
PT YCH Indonesia Group is the leading integrated end-to-end supply chain management and logistics partner to some of the world’s largest companies. YCH Group’s suite of innovative award-winning end-to-end supply chain management solutions - Intribution, Intrabution, Retrogistics, Y-Merge and V-Hub- employ cutting edge web-technologies that are best-in-class across industry clusters from consumer and electronics to chemical and healthcare, to deliver powerful competitive advantages for customers
Job Description :
Develop and implement a strategy for the continuous improvement of logistics services within Indonesia regions organization of internal KPI and measurements with a common reporting structure, and the identification and development of people and capabilities Lead the implementation/expansion of new/existing electronics operations across the region in order to facilitate knowledge exchange and the sharing of best practices Identify suitable targets and support the development of reliable, sustainable and profitable logistics services, including the areas of People, Process, Layout/Zoning, System, Cost Controls including Maintenance and Consumables, Quality, Safety and Compliance and Internal/External KPIs Act as subject matter expert for electronic Logistics Operations-related inquiries The incumbent is responsible for Logistic Operations that includes best-in-class warehousing, distribution, operations and value-added services in support of the Electronics Logistics Operations across Indonesia. This role also focuses on the continuous drive towards Operations Excellence and Quality service, and is measured by improvements made to productivity, staff motivation and KPI
Requirements
Minimum bachelor degree or higher degree preferably major in Transport, Logistics, Business Management, Electronics or relevant technical field At least 3 years of working experience in related area, preferably in 3PL or Supply chain company Excellent in operating computer Have good interpersonal, communication, planning, and negotiation skills Good command of English both oral and written  is a must Trained in Quality Management Systems/GDP/GMP or equivalent Experience in the use and application of computerized warehouse and distribution management systems Effective communication and presentation skills Willing to be stationed in Manado Willing to travel across the region
All applications will be treated confidentially & only short listed candidates will be notified
